<paragraph blockId="193.[151,1437,1590,2013]" lastBlockId="194.[199,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="194" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[272,529,1806,1833]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="1" refId="ref368514" refString="Rondani, C. (1859 b) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: III. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars secunda: Muscidae, Siphoninae et (partim) Tachininae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 243 + [1] p., 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1859">Rondani (1859b: 206)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[656,798,1806,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Mesomelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[656,798,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Mesomelena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and identified 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1848" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesomelaena">
<emphasis box="[1178,1436,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Metopia mesomelaena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." box="[199,332,1842,1869]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="377 - 378" refId="ref356490" refString="Loew, H. (1848) Eine neue europaische Art der Gattung Metopia. Entomologische Zeitung, 9, 377 - 378." type="journal article" year="1848">Loew, 1848</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[414,462,1843,1869]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">type</typeStatus>
species. Having used the species epithet for the new nominal genus and thinking that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[199,501,1878,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Mesomelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesomelaena">
<emphasis box="[199,501,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Mesomelena mesomelaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was incorrect, Rondani incorrectly substituted it with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[1118,1335,1878,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Mesomelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewii">
<emphasis box="[1118,1335,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Mesomelena loewii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schiner, I. R." pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="441 - 656" refId="ref372602" refString="Schiner, I. R. (1861 b) Fauna Austriaca. Die Fliegen (Diptera). Nach der analytischen Methode bearbeitet, mit der Characteristik sammtlicher europaischer Gattungen, der Beschreibung aller in Deutschland vorkommenden Arten und der Aufzahlung aller bisher beschriebene europaischen Arten. I. Theil. [Heft 6 / 7]. C. Gerold's Sohn, Wien, pp. 441 - 656. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8525" type="book chapter" year="1861">Schiner (1861b: 501)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M. &amp; Stein, P." box="[365,673,1914,1941]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="1 - 747" refId="ref346041" refString="Bezzi, M. &amp; Stein, P. (1907) Cyclorrapha Aschiza. Cyclorrapha Schizophora: Schizometopa. In: Becker, T., Bezzi, M., Kertesz, K. &amp; Stein, P. (Eds.), Katalog der palaarktischen Dipteren. Band III. G. Wesselenyi in Hodmezovasarhely, Budapest, pp. 1 - 747." type="book chapter" year="1907">Bezzi &amp; Stein (1907: 515)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B." box="[734,1013,1914,1941]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="177 - 232" refId="ref366661" refString="Rohdendorf, B. (1975) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region. Band XI. Lieferung. 311. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 177 - 232." type="book chapter" year="1975">Rohdendorf (1975: 186)</bibRefCitation>
placed this name in synonymy with 
<emphasis box="[199,505,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[199,501,1950,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Mesomelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesomelaena">Mesomelena mesomelaena</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
while 
<bibRefCitation author="Brauer, F. &amp; Bergenstamm, J. E. von" box="[578,976,1950,1977]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="69 - 180" refId="ref346619" refString="Brauer, F. &amp; Bergenstamm, J. E. von (1889) Die Zweiflugler der Kaiserlichen Museums zu Wien. IV. Vorarbeiten zu einer Monographie der Muscaria Schizometopa (exclusive Anthomyidae). Pars I. Denkschriften der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften. Wien. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe, 56 (1), 69 - 180, 11 pls." type="journal article" year="1889">Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm (1889: 178)</bibRefCitation>
considered it as a valid species. The 
<typeStatus box="[1377,1436,1951,1977]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">types</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[238,406,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewii">
<emphasis box="[238,406,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Metopia loewii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be the same as for the name it was proposed to replace, i.e., 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1129,1429,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Mesomelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesomelaena">
<emphasis box="[1129,1429,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Mesomelena mesomelaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[252,300,151,177]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">type</typeStatus>
material of this latter species should be in Loew’s collection in the MNHUB. In Loew’s collection under the label 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1848" box="[374,626,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesomelaena">
<emphasis box="[374,626,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">Metopia mesomelaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is only 
<specimenCount box="[781,905,187,213]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
(in good condition) (J. Pohl, pers. comm., 
<date pageId="194" pageNumber="195" value="2020-07">July 2020</date>
) which cannot be the 
<typeStatus box="[499,547,223,249]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">type</typeStatus>
because 
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." box="[648,849,223,249]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" pagination="377 - 378" refId="ref356490" refString="Loew, H. (1848) Eine neue europaische Art der Gattung Metopia. Entomologische Zeitung, 9, 377 - 378." type="journal article" year="1848">Loew (1848: 378)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the single female of his collection had the abdomen destroyed. Under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[617,786,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewii">
<emphasis box="[617,786,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">Metopia loewii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is 
<specimenCount box="[882,1005,259,285]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
(non-type) in the MZUF.
</paragraph>
